  "description": "Admin push-land effect dashboard (/admin/coord/lands) from push-land Phase 4 (web #425), extended by the multi-repo cascade consumer (web #457, coord producer coord#339): LandCard now renders a cross-repo badge when a land signature carries a correlation_id, expanding into a composed cross-repo verdict panel, and LandPreviewPanel renders one sibling-cascade card per predicted.sibling_cascades entry. Three live sections: pre-land impact preview (repo+PR form), recent declared lands (30s poll), and per-dimension predictor calibration. metadata.routeStubs is load-bearing for the multi-repo affordances: prod/CI backends have no multi-repo land rows, so the lands-list stub returns one land row WITH a correlation_id + sibling_cascades + a settled verification, which makes the cross-repo badge (the #457 code path) render statically on page load. Stub precedence relies on Playwright's last-registered-wins route matching: the broad '**/api/v1/operations/lands**' list stub is registered FIRST (lowest precedence) and the specific /precision, /preview, and /verifications stubs after it, so each sub-path gets its own shape (a '?'-glob list pattern failed to match in CI - avoided entirely). The precision endpoint is stubbed with the live-prod zero-data shape (4 dimensions, null rates -> 'no data yet' cells) because the panel derives its rows FROM the response (an empty dimensions array renders no table at all) and the broad list pattern would otherwise swallow the call; its assertions are structure-only (table + header cells). Authored from a live authed in-process UI Bridge snapshot (135 instrumented elements, route /admin/coord/lands) captured 2026-06-05. Read-only; structural only. The click-to-expand verdict panel and preview-run sibling cards are interaction-gated and covered by component tests (LandCard.test.ts / LandPreviewPanel.render.test.tsx) rather than transitions - no house spec exercises the transition executor yet.",
